  <title>HPE Helion 2.0 Development Platform: Monitoring Messaging</title>
  <body>
    <p>Each service team has configured alarms for its service. This page documents the recommended
      troubleshooting steps for each alarm.</p>
   <section><title>Cue</title>
      <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_jsq_hqs_wt">
           <tgroup cols="4">
          <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1"/>
          <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2"/>
          <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3"/>
          <colspec colname="c4" colnum="4"/>
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Alarm Name</entry>
              <entry>Description</entry>
              <entry>Likely Cause</entry>
              <entry>Mitigation Tasks to Perform</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>HTTP Status </entry>
              <entry>component=cue-api</entry>
              <entry> API is unresponsive </entry>
              <entry>Restart Apache </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Process Check </entry>
              <entry>process_name=cue-worker </entry>
              <entry>Supervisor stopped </entry>
              <entry>Use supervisor to start all workers </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Process Check </entry>
              <entry>process_name=cue-monitor</entry>
              <entry>Process crashed</entry>
              <entry>Restart cue-monitor service </entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
    </section><section><title>RabbitMQ</title>
      <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1">
        <tgroup cols="4">
          <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
          <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1.25*"/>
          <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" colwidth="1.56*"/>
          <colspec colname="c4" colnum="4" colwidth="2.41*"/>
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Alarm Name</entry>
              <entry>Description</entry>
              <entry>Likely Cause</entry>
              <entry>Mitigation Tasks to Perform</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>Process Check  </entry>
              <entry>rabbitmq-server process not running</entry>
              <entry> Process crashed. </entry>
              <entry>
                <ul id="ul_u2p_3ts_wt">
                  <li>Restart process on affected node.</li>
                  <li>Review logs to determine cause.</li>
                </ul>
              </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>RabbitMQ Queue Depth </entry>
              <entry>Alarms when the depth of the message queue is high. </entry>
              <entry>
                <ul id="ul_s1v_lts_wt">
                  <li>System load or a slow/failed consumer.</li>
                  <li>If only a single queue is slowing, the consumer could be down. </li>
                </ul>
              </entry>
              <entry>Look for high load throughout the system. This alarm can fire for multiple
                queues and multiple machines. Finding out which ones it fired on will help determine
                the cause. </entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup></table>
    
    </section>
